
[1]grievously

   GRIE'VOUSLY, adv. With pain; painfully; with great pain or distress;
   as, to be grievously afflicted.

   1. With discontent, ill will or grief.

   2. Calamitously; miserably; greatly; with great uneasiness, distress or
   grief.

   3. Atrociously; as, to sin or offend grievously.
